             Rear Admiral Grace Hopper            
                      * * *                       
Fifty years ago, each computer maker used  its own
programming  languages to tell a computer what  to
do. In 1959, a group of programmers devised COBOL,
a  COmmon,  Business-Oriented  Language.  Programs
written   in   COBOL   could  run on more than one
manufacturer’s computer.
In a 1960   test,  the same COBOL   programs   ran
successfully on   two computers built by different
manufacturers.
(americanhistory.si.edu: COBOL)
